featureType.title: Seamap Australia - WA - Seagrass Synthesis 2023 (INCLUDES PRIVATE DATA)
featureType.abstract:
This data collection is an aggregated product of individual seagrass surveys conducted by various organisations in southern WA. This dataset includes PRIVATE data from WA DWER and is *NOT FOR DOWNLOAD*, but may be used for display purposes.
The Web Feature Service (WFS) has been intentionally disabled from this layer.
This map package shows all survey data from 1988 through to 2023. Only data collated by the ACEAS group (prior to 2013) may be downloaded from this site, see 'SeamapAus_WA_seagrass_synthesis_2013'.
Surveys conducted prior to 2013 were undertaken by the Department of Water (DoW), Western Australian Government, Geoscience Australia, and Murdoch University Marine and Freshwater Research Laboratory (MAFR). This data was acquired by the ACEAS Seagrass Group for their 2013 Australia-wide risk assessment of Seagrass.
Subsequent data is available for several locations around southern WA, in addition to new monitoring sites, from the WA Department of Water and Environmental Regulation (DWER). See the https://data.gov.au for download access to more recent survey data.
